future environment and at the same time enable new business opportunities for manufacturers.

SERBIT stands for SERvice Based Information Technology and is our view on what is needed from an IT standpoint to support the business case of selling products as a service.

Selling products as a service will become a necessity if we are to save our only planet but it will not happen over night. We need to start thinking repair instead of re-buy, retrofit instead of waste . For this we need the right set of tools to support our journey.

The end goal is a circular business economy that enables OEMs to increase lifecycle span and at the same time earn more money as well as have less environmental footprint. In order to do this we need to follow up machine individuals and we need 3 main technical platforms enabled:

Accrue data
Machine need to be equipped with sensors that preent relevant data streams. Thereafter machine is linked to internet, bluetooth or other relevant protocol to share the data.

Assemble and Analyze data
A platform to accrue the data sent by each machine, translate the data into an understandable form, trigger events and similar. Also a level of machnine leraning can be included to analyze the data and predict failures. 

Experience and Integrate data
A platform to consume data and present the information to the service field for repair and maintenance. The presentation layer shall be easy to consume via phone or iPAD. Assembe documentation along with spare part information also trigger purchase of spares.</gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2019-10-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/E18E2F0F-AC7D-4E02-9559-669F7C8FEC74"><gtr:id>E18E2F0F-AC7D-4E02-9559-669F7C8FEC74</gtr:id><gtr:name>Innovate UK</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2016-11-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>146721</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">600323</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects/><gtr:researchTopics><gtr:researchTopic><gtr:id>D05BC2E0-0345-4A3F-8C3F-775BC42A0819</gtr:id><gtr:text>Unclassified</gtr:text></gtr:researchTopic></gtr:researchTopics><gtr:rcukProgrammes/></gtr:project></gtr:projectComposition></gtr:projectOverview>